result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason John Paschel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jason John Paschel is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jason John Paschel was found guilty of Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.
  • Jason John Paschel was found guilty of Manufacture/Deliver Heroin(>3-10g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)2.
  • Jason John Paschel was found guilty of OWI (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:45 am case called. Defendant Jason John Paschel in court with attorney Sandra J. Zenor.  Defendant Jason John Paschel in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court makes statement regarding status of case and matter before court. Court addresses plea on Count 3.   Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright Count 4. All matters now procedurally at the same point. Statement by defendants girlfriend to court. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Zenor. Statement by defendant. Court makes a statement prior to sentencing. Court sentences the defendant to: COUNT 1 & 2- 7 years Wisconsin State Prison to be served as 3 year Initial Confinement and 4 year Extended Supervision. Concurrent to each other and concurrent to Wood County 16CF135. Credit for 2 day served. CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through, Absolute Sobriety, not to be on the premises of any bars, defendant is not to possess/ingest any impairing substance unless prescribed by a treating physician. Terms of Agent. Costs to include $1400 Drug Buy Reimbursement money to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Court orders DOC authorization. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Court finds defendant eligible for Challenge Incarceration and Substance Abuse Programs. COUNT 3-150 days WCJ, concurrent to Count 1 & 2 and concurrent to Wood County 16CF135. $2500 fine to be paid through DOC authorization. 35 month DL revocation, 35 month IID, OWI assessment. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given.
